# Data & security

- Supabase Auth `user_id` on every table. Row-level security policies on all
  tables; a user can never read or write another user's rows.
- No third-party analytics, trackers, or telemetry anywhere in the app.
- Never expose the Supabase service-role key to the client. Server-only secrets
  stay in server code / route handlers.
- Wearable OAuth tokens live in isolated columns prepared for encryption. Never
  store raw tokens in plaintext.
- The crash definition is stored as versioned rows (`crash_rule_versions`) with
  an active-from date. Each crash references the rule version active when it
  occurred. Never silently relabel historical crashes when the rule changes;
  re-running history under a new rule is an explicit, visible action.
- `note_tags` (LLM-derived) require user confirmation before counting as data,
  and sending notes to an LLM is gated behind
  `user_settings.llm_notes_enabled` (default false).
- Days flagged crash / illness / vaccine are excluded from baselines via
  `is_excluded`.
- Prefer SQL migrations checked into the repo; keep the schema in sync with §3
  of `docs/implementation-plan.md`.
